#: ascension.tra:82729
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Upon parting paths with <CHARNAME>, Viconia wandered for a great deal of time.  She still met with ignorance and hatred from those who knew of her kind, but Viconia was determined now more than ever to establish herself as seperate from the legacy of the dark elves.  She had been to the deepest planes of hell and fought side-by-side with <CHARNAME> as <PRO_HESHE> became a God... and she would hide her face from the surface lands any longer.  Even when Shar, her goddess of darkness and loss, abandoned her completely Viconia was unrepetant.  Tales of her grew as she made her presence felt in one land after another... often as a savior, only to be thanklessly driven out by suspicion and fear.  Still Viconia traveled on, refusing the company of fellow travelers and adventurers and never finding anywhere that she could truly name a home.  Her destiny was her own, and she would seek it on her own terms.\n"
#| "What eventually become of Viconia is unknown.  Her greatest legend is also the most unlikely, although its persistence gives it some credit.  It is said that Viconia saved the elves of Suldanessalar from a Zhentarim plot, fighting valiantly against the organization's agents... and in the end placing herself in harm's way to save Queen Ellesime from a deadly arrow.  Upon being revived, Viconia was surprised to discover that this last act had prompted the Suldanessalar elves to finally accept and forgive their drow sister.  Queen Ellesime granted the highest honors of the Seldarine to Viconia, the first drow ever honored so, and even invited Viconia to find a home in the Tree of Life once again.  Viconia was obviously moved by the gesture... and while she considered the Queen's offer, it is said she eventually merely bowed deeply to Ellesime and silently left Suldanessalar forever.  Viconia was never reported seen again."
msgid ""
"Upon parting paths with <CHARNAME>, Viconia wandered for a great deal of time. She still met with ignorance and hatred from those who knew of her kind, but Viconia was determined now more than ever to establish herself as seperate from the legacy of the dark elves. She had been to the deepest planes of hell and fought side-by-side with <CHARNAME> as <PRO_HESHE> became a God... and she would hide her face from the surface lands any longer. Even when Shar, her goddess of darkness and loss, abandoned her completely Viconia was unrepetant. Tales of her grew as she made her presence felt in one land after another... often as a savior, only to be thanklessly driven out by suspicion and fear. Still Viconia traveled on, refusing the company of fellow travelers and adventurers and never finding anywhere that she could truly name a home. Her destiny was her own, and she would seek it on her own terms.\n"
"What eventually become of Viconia is unknown. Her greatest legend is also the most unlikely, although its persistence gives it some credit. It is said that Viconia saved the elves of Suldanessalar from a Zhentarim plot, fighting valiantly against the organization's agents... and in the end placing herself in harm's way to save Queen Ellesime from a deadly arrow. Upon being revived, Viconia was surprised to discover that this last act had prompted the Suldanessalar elves to finally accept and forgive their drow sister. Queen Ellesime granted the highest honors of the Seldarine to Viconia, the first drow ever honored so, and even invited Viconia to find a home in the Tree of Life once again. Viconia was obviously moved by the gesture... and while she considered the Queen's offer, it is said she eventually merely bowed deeply to Ellesime and silently left Suldanessalar forever. Viconia was never reported seen again."
msgstr ""
"Da quando la sua strada non fu più la stessa di <CHARNAME>, Viconia viaggiò a lungo. Si scontrò ancora con l'ignoranza e l'odio di coloro che conoscevano la sua razza, ma Viconia fu più che mai decisa a dimostrarsi diversa dagli altri efli scuri. Era stata nei piani più profondi dell'inferno e aveva combattuto fianco a fianco con <CHARNAME> quando divenne un dio... e non avrebbe nascosto il suo viso nelle terre di superficie mai più. Persino quando Shar, la sua signora dell'oscurità e della perdita, la abbandonò del tutto Viconia non si pentì. Le storie su di lei crebbero... spesso era una salvatrice, ma solo per essere alla fine gentilmente invitata ad andarsene per sospetto e paura. Tuttavia Viconia continuò a viaggiare, rifiutando la compagnia di avventurieri e senza mai trovare un luogo che potesse davvero chiamare casa. Il suo destino le apparteneva, e l'avrebbe cercato alle sue condizioni.\n"
"Ciò che poi fu di Viconia è ignoto. La sua più grande leggenda è anche quella più inverosimile, sebbene la sua perseveranza possa darle qualche credibilità. Si dice che Viconia salvò gli elfi di Suldanessalar da un complotto Zhentarim, combattendo con valore contro i membri dell'organizzazione... e alla fine mettendosi nella traiettoria tra la regina Ellesime e una freccia mortale salvandola. Dopo essere stata rianimata, Viconia fu sorpresa di scoprire che la sua ultima azione la fece finalmente accettare e perdonare dai suoi fratelli elfi di Suldanessalar. La regina Ellesime le diede i più alti onori, la prima drow a riceverli, e la invitò addirittura a trovare casa sull'Albero della Vita ancora una volta. Viconia fu ovviamente commossa dal gesto... e mentre stava riflettendo sull'offerta della regina, si dice che alla fine semplicemente s'inchinò profondamente e lasciò in silenzio Suldanessalar per sempre. Di Viconia non ci fu più alcuna traccia."

