msgid ""
"In the years following his resurrection by <CHARNAME>, Sarevok spent many "
"years wandering throughout the Forgotten Realms, rarely spending much time "
"in any single place. In Berdusk he is said to have routed an army of "
"invading orcs, displaying such fearsome power and rage that terrified locals"
" weren't sure whom to fear more... only to disappear quietly without "
"expecting a reward. In Westgate he arrived as conqueror, brutally enforcing "
"his will over the city only to mysteriously vanish months later, leaving his"
" own startled men to the mercies of the angry mobs. He acted like a man that"
" did not know himself, and all the stories agreed that Sarevok was a "
"tortured soul, balanced between life and death, never to achieve either. "
"Those who knew Sarevok best, which were few, said that the tormented warrior"
" would in turn curse the fabled <CHARNAME> for giving him his second "
"chance... and then thank <PRO_HIMHER>. Eventually he disappeared entirely "
"from the Realms, said to have assaulted the Abyss itself or even taken his "
"own life. In truth, he journeyed to Kara-Tur to bury his one true love, the "
"warrior Tamoko. He never returned, though the stories endure."
msgstr ""
"Negli anni successivi alla sua resurrezione da parte di <CHARNAME>, Sarevok "
"passò molti anni viaggiando nei Reami Dimenticati, rimanendo raramente a "
"lungo in un solo posto. Si dice che a Berdusk respinse un'armata di orchi "
"invasori, mostrando terrificanti poteri e una furia tale che i cittadini "
"terrorizzati non sapevano chi temere di più... salvo poi scomparire nel "
"silenzio senza pretendere una ricompensa. A Westgate giunse come un "
"conquistatore, imponendo brutalmente il suo volere sulla città per poi "
"scomparire misteriosamente mesi dopo, lasciando i suoi stessi uomini "
"sbigottiti alla mercè della folla infuriata. Agì come un uomo che non "
"conosceva se stesso, e tutte le storie sul suo conto concordano sul fatto "
"che fosse un'anima tormentata, in bilico tra la vita e la morte, senza mai "
"raggiungerne una. Coloro che lo conobbero meglio, pochi, affermano che il "
"guerriero tormentato a volte maledisse il leggendario <CHARNAME> per avergli"
" dato una seconda occasione... e che a volte lo ringraziasse. Alla fine "
"scomparse del tutto dai Reami. Voci lo vollero all'assaltato dello stesso "
"Abisso o forse decise di mettere fine alla sue sofferenze. In verità, "
"viaggiò per Kara-Tur per seppelire il suo unico vero amore, la guerriera "
"Tamoko. Non tornò mai più, sebbene le storie continuino."

#: ascension.tra:82724
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Nalia grew quite powerful after her association with <CHARNAME>.  Initially she traveled, slaking her thirst for magical lore by associating with some of the greatest wizards across the Realms.  She sought to use her great power to bring justice to the land, but over time found that if her time with <CHARNAME> had taught her anything, it is that such power must be tempered with wisdom or it is useless.  She could strike out at evil as she wished... it did not always help the needy, as she thought it would, and after a year of travel she remembered that there was a far better way that she could be of service to her people.\n"
#| "Nalia returned to Amn and her family home of de'Arnise Hold.  She found it in the control of none other than Isaea Roenal, but she was no longer the wayward child that he expected, and single-handedly brought him to justice for his indiscretions.  She declared herself the inheritor of her father's ducal title, and for once there was no argument from the local nobility.  They snubbed her and her magic, and initially rejoiced when the Cowled Wizards sought to remove her from power.  Nalia demonstrated to them all that she was no-one to trifle with, however, and the Cowled Wizards learned to fear her name.  Over time Nalia became a beloved ruler, respected archmage, and eventually earned a seat on the Amnish Council of Six itself.  The nobility grew to rely on Nalia's leadership, and she would become a prominent figure in Amn for many years, constantly fighting for the good of the common folk and making many frustrated enemies among the nobility and Cowled Wizards both.  Nalia would die many years later, surrounded by a loving family... her last words would be to thank <CHARNAME> for so long ago showing her the true path she needed to walk."
msgid ""
"Nalia grew quite powerful after her association with <CHARNAME>. Initially she traveled, slaking her thirst for magical lore by associating with some of the greatest wizards across the Realms. She sought to use her great power to bring justice to the land, but over time found that if her time with <CHARNAME> had taught her anything, it is that such power must be tempered with wisdom or it is useless. She could strike out at evil as she wished... it did not always help the needy, as she thought it would, and after a year of travel she remembered that there was a far better way that she could be of service to her people.\n"
"Nalia returned to Amn and her family home of de'Arnise Hold. She found it in the control of none other than Isaea Roenal, but she was no longer the wayward child that he expected, and single-handedly brought him to justice for his indiscretions. She declared herself the inheritor of her father's ducal title, and for once there was no argument from the local nobility. They snubbed her and her magic, and initially rejoiced when the Cowled Wizards sought to remove her from power. Nalia demonstrated to them all that she was no-one to trifle with, however, and the Cowled Wizards learned to fear her name. Over time Nalia became a beloved ruler, respected archmage, and eventually earned a seat on the Amnish Council of Six itself. The nobility grew to rely on Nalia's leadership, and she would become a prominent figure in Amn for many years, constantly fighting for the good of the common folk and making many frustrated enemies among the nobility and Cowled Wizards both. Nalia would die many years later, surrounded by a loving family... her last words would be to thank <CHARNAME> for so long ago showing her the true path she needed to walk."
msgstr ""
"Nalia divenne piuttosto potente dopo aver lasciato <CHARNAME>. All'inizio "
"viaggiò, placando la sua sete di conoscenza di magia unendosi ad alcuni dei "
"più potenti maghi di tutti i Reami. Cercò di usare i suoi grandi poteri "
"magici per portare ovunque giustizia, ma col passare del tempo scoprì che se"
" il tempo con <CHARNAME> le aveva insegnato qualcosa, è che un simile potere"
" deve essere temperato dalla saggezza o è inutile. Poter annientare il male "
"come desideri... non sempre aiuta i bisognosi, come invece pensava, e dopo "
"un anno di viaggi si ricordò che c'era un modo migliore in cui poteva essere"
" a servizio della sua gente. Nalia tornò nell'Amn nel castello della sua "
"famiglia de'Arnise. Scoprì che questo era caduto sotto il controllo assoluto"
" di Isaea Roenal. Ma Nalia non era più la bambina ribelle che costui si "
"aspettava, anzi, da sola lo costrinse al confronto per il suo gesto "
"sconsiderato. Si dichiarò l'unica erede del titolo ducale paterno, ed una "
"volta per tutte non ci furono più discussioni dai nobili locali. Snobbarono "
"lei e la sua magia, e all'inizio gioirono quando gli Stregoni Incappucciati "
"tentarono di rimuoverla dal potere. Ma Nalia dimostrò a tutti loro che non "
"era una con cui scherzare, e i Maghi Incappuciati impararono a temere il suo"
" nome. Con il tempo Nalia divenne un governante amato, un'arcimaga "
"rispettata e alla fine si guadagnò un posto nel Consiglio dei Sei dell'Amn. "
"La nobiltà iniziò a contare sulla guida di Nalia, e divenne una figura di "
"spicco dell'Amn per molti anni, combattendo costantemente per il bene della "
"gente comune e creandosi numerosi nemici frustrati sia tra le file dei "
"nobili che degli Stregoni Incapucciati. Nalia morì molti anni più tardi, "
"circondata da una affettuosa famiglia... le sue ultime parole furono per "
"ringraziare <CHARNAME>, per averle mostrato così tanto tempo fa il giusto "
"sentiero che aveva bisogno di intraprendere."

#: ascension.tra:82723
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "The perils that Mazzy Fentan faced at the side of <CHARNAME> did nothing to "
#| "dissuade her thirst for adventure.  In fact, it was not long after the "
#| "events in Tethyr that she formed the Fentan Knights, a stalwart band of "
#| "heroes that spawned tales across the Realms.  Always Mazzy invoked the name "
#| "of <CHARNAME> when urging her comrades to valour, or when they battled doubt"
#| " and temptation.  <CHARNAME> was the greatest <PRO_MANWOMAN> that Mazzy had "
