#: ascension.tra:82714
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Aerie continued adventuring after years after leaving <CHARNAME>'s company, "
#| "often traveling with a larger group but sometimes striking out on her own to"
#| " use her considerable power to fight against slavery in the Realms.  Her "
#| "compassion grew tainted by revenge, however; revenge for what had been taken"
#| " from her when she was in chains and could never be restored.  She might "
#| "have lost herself to her vengeance entirely had fortune not smiled upon her."
#| "  The tale goes that Aerie, filled with a righteous fury, destroyed a slaver"
#| " enclave in the northern hills of Cormyr single-handedly.  She was surprised"
#| " to find a group of avariel elves that had been held captive there and "
#| "quickly freed them, and was in turn invited to return to her long-lost home "
#| "of Faenya-Dail.  She learned much while she was there.  Most importantly, "
#| "she learned she was no longer truly one of avariel, and let go forever of "
#| "the wings that she had lost. Faenya-Dail was no longer her home, and it was "
#| "with mixed emotions that she bid it farewell.  It is said that Aerie "
#| "eventually became a high priestess in Understone, a gnomish village her "
#| "mentor Quayle had sometimes spoken of.  He had been her true family, and it "
#| "was among his people that she finally found happiness and the family she had"
#| " always longed for.  It was also said that Aerie prayed for her old friend, "
#| "<CHARNAME>, each night as the stars revealed themselves in the sky above.  "
#| "She sincerely hoped her friend had been fortunate enough to find the peace "
#| "that she had... for without <CHARNAME>, it would never have been possible."
msgid ""
"Aerie continued adventuring after years after leaving <CHARNAME>'s company, "
"often traveling with a larger group but sometimes striking out on her own to"
" use her considerable power to fight against slavery in the Realms. Her "
"compassion grew tainted by revenge, however; revenge for what had been taken"
" from her when she was in chains and could never be restored. She might have"
" lost herself to her vengeance entirely had fortune not smiled upon her. The"
" tale goes that Aerie, filled with a righteous fury, destroyed a slaver "
"enclave in the northern hills of Cormyr single-handedly. She was surprised "
"to find a group of avariel elves that had been held captive there and "
"quickly freed them, and was in turn invited to return to her long-lost home "
"of Faenya-Dail. She learned much while she was there. Most importantly, she "
"learned she was no longer truly one of avariel, and let go forever of the "
"wings that she had lost. Faenya-Dail was no longer her home, and it was with"
" mixed emotions that she bid it farewell. It is said that Aerie eventually "
"became a high priestess in Understone, a gnomish village her mentor Quayle "
"had sometimes spoken of. He had been her true family, and it was among his "
"people that she finally found happiness and the family she had always longed"
" for. It was also said that Aerie prayed for her old friend, <CHARNAME>, "
"each night as the stars revealed themselves in the sky above. She sincerely "
"hoped her friend had been fortunate enough to find the peace that she had..."
" for without <CHARNAME>, it would never have been possible."
msgstr ""
"Aerie continuò a fare l'avventuriera per anni dopo aver lasciato la "
"compagnia di <CHARNAME>, spesso viaggiando con un gruppo ampio o per conto "
"suo usando il suo notevole potere per combattere la schiavitù nei Reami. La "
"sua compassione però crebbe macchiata dal sentimento di vendetta; vendetta "
"per ciò che le era stato strappato quando era in catene e che mai avrebbe "
"potuto riavere. Si sarebbe persa completamente nella vendetta se la fortuna "
"non le avesse sorriso. La storia vuole che Aerie, piena di furia di "
"giustizia, distrusse un'enclave di schiavisti nelle colline a nord di Cormyr"
" tutta da sola. Fu sorpresa nel trovare un gruppo di elfi avariel che erano "
"stati catturati e li liberò immediatamente, e fu a sua volta invitata a far "
"ritorno nella sua casa da lungo perduta di Faenya-Dail. Imparò molto mentre "
"era lì. Soprattutto, imparò che non era più una vera avariel, e lasciò "
"andare per sempre le ali che aveva perduto. Faenya-Dail non era più casa "
"sua, e fu con sentimenti contrastanti che la salutò per sempre. Si dice che "
"Aerie alla fine divenne un'alta sacerdotessa di Understone, un villaggio di "
"gnomi del quale il suo mentore, Quayle, le aveva a volte parlato. Era stato "
"la sua vera famiglia, e tra la sua gente finalmente trovò la felicità e la "
"famiglia che aveva sempre desiderato. Si dice anche che Aerie pregò per il "
"suo vecchio amico, <CHARNAME>, tutte le notti quando le stelle si mostravano"
" nel cielo. Sperava sinceramente che il suo amico fosse stato abbastanza "
"fortunato da trovare la sua stessa pace... perchè senza <CHARNAME>, non "
"sarebbe mai stato possibile."

#: ascension.tra:82760
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Upon returning to Amkethran, Balthazar began to implement changes for the "
#| "better.  He had learned well from his friend and sibling the meaning of the "
#| "word \"Good\".  He carried his guilt with him always; a reminder never to "
#| "make the same mistakes again.  The remaining criminal elements were quickly "
#| "driven from his outpost, which attracted new settlers and merchants.   Over "
#| "the years, Amkethran grew into a thriving city and the cultural center of "
#| "the entire region, renown for its peace and compassion.   Balthazar was also"
#| " central in the creation of the Monastic Guard; an elite group of Paladins "
#| "and Monks that were sworn to protect the common folk from tyranny in any "
#| "form.  His deeds quickly earned him the respect and trust of his people.  In"
#| " Balthazar's advanced years, his work finished, it was said he could be "
#| "found most often gazing at the night sky and remembering <CHARNAME>.  Later,"
#| " Balthazar would leave Amkethran forever on a pilgrimage to Candlekeep......"
#| " to give a final thanks for the peace he had found and to see for himself "
#| "the humble beginnings of a legend."
msgid ""
"Upon returning to Amkethran, Balthazar began to implement changes for the "
"better. He had learned well from his friend and sibling the meaning of the "
"word \"Good\". He carried his guilt with him always; a reminder never to "
"make the same mistakes again. The remaining criminal elements were quickly "
"driven from his outpost, which attracted new settlers and merchants. Over "
"the years, Amkethran grew into a thriving city and the cultural center of "
"the entire region, renown for its peace and compassion. Balthazar was also "
"central in the creation of the Monastic Guard; an elite group of Paladins "
"and Monks that were sworn to protect the common folk from tyranny in any "
"form. His deeds quickly earned him the respect and trust of his people. In "
"Balthazar's advanced years, his work finished, it was said he could be found"
" most often gazing at the night sky and remembering <CHARNAME>. Later, "
"Balthazar would leave Amkethran forever on a pilgrimage to Candlekeep... to "
"give a final thanks for the peace he had found and to see for himself the "
"humble beginnings of a legend."
msgstr ""
"Dopo essere ritornato ad Amkethran, Balthazar iniziò a portare cambiamenti "
"per il meglio. Aveva ben imparato dal suo amico e fratello il significato "
"della parola \"Bontà\". Portò con sè le sue colpe per sempre; un ricordo per"
" non commettere nuovamente gli stessi errori. Ciò che ancora rimaneva di "
"criminale fu velocemente estirpato dall'avamposto, il quale attrasse nuovi "
"coloni e mercanti. Con gli anni, Amkethran divenne una città fiorente e il "
"centro culturale dell'intera regione, famosa per la sua pace e compassione. "
"Balthazar fu anche di centrale importanza per la creazione delle Guardia "
"Monastica; un gruppo di paladini e monaci d'elite che giurò di proteggere il"
" popolo da qualsiasi forma di tirannia. Le sue azioni gli fecero presto "
"guadagnare il rispetto e la fiducia della sua gente. Nei suoi ultimi anni, "
"il suo lavoro finì, e si dice che fu spesso trovato ad ammirare il cielo "
"ricordando <CHARNAME>. In seguito, Balthazar lasciò Amkethran per sempre per"
" un pellegrinaggio a Candlekeep...... per ringraziare un'ultima volta per la"
" pace che aveva trovato e per vedere le umili origini di una leggenda."

#: ascension.tra:82785
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Bodhi had tasted godlike power in the form of <CHARNAME>'s soul.  As the "
#| "last vestiges of it faded with time, she began to desire more, slipping into"
#| " bitter hatred as it became her obsession to reach such heights again.  "
#| "People up and down the Sword Coast came to know fear as Bodhi bathed in "
#| "their blood, sating her thirst for chaos and death.  Villages began to leave"
#| " people bound by the road as an offering to the thing that stalked the "
#| "night.  Her name became a byword for terror, with temples far and wide "
#| "trying in vain to hunt her down.  Many a mighty cleric was later found "
#| "drained of blood, agony etched across their pallid features.  Over time "
#| "Bodhi felt the icy grip of the curse tighten its hold on her.  Desperation "
#| "mixed with fear clawed at the very fibre of her being.  Desire for chaos "
#| "faded and she fought to survive once more.  Ambiton, which had once prompted"
#| " her to whisper dreams of power into the ear of her brother, now brought her"
#| " back to the place she had long ago called home, Suldanessellar.  It was at "
#| "the gates that Ellesime met her.  At the gates that Bodhi danced one last "
#| "time.  Revenge burned bright in both of them, and it called out for blood.  "
#| "The power of the Tree of Life drove Bodhi on, and the memory of Joneleth "
#| "cried out to Ellesime.  The two embraced, and it was revenge that was "
#| "destined to be the victor, even as a stake pierced the still black heart of "
#| "Bodhi, one who was as damned in life as she was in death."
msgid ""
"Bodhi had tasted godlike power in the form of <CHARNAME>'s soul. As the last"
" vestiges of it faded with time, she began to desire more, slipping into "
"bitter hatred as it became her obsession to reach such heights again. People"
" up and down the Sword Coast came to know fear as Bodhi bathed in their "
"blood, sating her thirst for chaos and death. Villages began to leave people"
" bound by the road as an offering to the thing that stalked the night. Her "
"name became a byword for terror, with temples far and wide trying in vain to"
" hunt her down. Many a mighty cleric was later found drained of blood, agony"
" etched across their pallid features. Over time Bodhi felt the icy grip of "
"the curse tighten its hold on her. Desperation mixed with fear clawed at the"
" very fibre of her being. Desire for chaos faded and she fought to survive "
"once more. Ambiton, which had once prompted her to whisper dreams of power "
"into the ear of her brother, now brought her back to the place she had long "
"ago called home, Suldanessellar. It was at the gates that Ellesime met her. "
"At the gates that Bodhi danced one last time. Revenge burned bright in both "
"of them, and it called out for blood. The power of the Tree of Life drove "
"Bodhi on, and the memory of Joneleth cried out to Ellesime. The two "
"embraced, and it was revenge that was destined to be the victor, even as a "
"stake pierced the still black heart of Bodhi, one who was as damned in life "
"as she was in death."
msgstr ""
"Bodhi aveva assaporato il potere divino con l'anima di <CHARNAME>. Quando le"
" ultime tracce di esso svanirono con il tempo, Bodhi iniziò a desiderarne "
"ancora, scivolando in un più aspro odio quando la sua ossessione divenne "
"raggiungere nuovamente una simile vetta. La gente di tutta la Costa della "
"Spada conobbe la paura quando Bodhi iniziò a far il bagno nel loro sangue, "
"saziando la sua sete di caos e morte. I villaggi iniziarono a lasciare gente"
" legata al di fuori delle mura come offerta per la cosa che si aggirava di "
"notte. Il suo nome divenne il simbolo del terrore, con templi di ogni luogo "
"che cercarono invano di braccarla. Molti potenti sacerdoti furono trovati "
"senza una goccia di sangue, con il terrore impresso nei loro pallidi volti. "
"Con il tempo Bodhi fu abbandonata dal gelido morso della maledizione che la "
"stringeva. Disperazione unita alla paura dilaniarono la stessa fibra del suo"
" essere. Il desiderio per il caos scemò e combattè per sopravvivere ancora "
"una volta. L'ambizione, che una volta le fece sussurrare sogni di potere "
"nelle orecchie del fratello, ora la stava riportando al luogo che una volta "
"era solita chiamare casa, Suldanessellar. Fu ai cancelli che Ellesime la "
"incontrò. Ai cancelli Bodhi scrisse la sua storia per l'ultima volta. La "
"vendetta bruciava in entrambe, ed essa pretese il sangue. Il potere "
"dell'Albero della Vita mosse Bodhi, e la memoria di Joneleth invocò ad alta "
"voce Ellesime. Le due si abbracciarono, poichè era la vendetta la vincitrice"
" destinata, anche quando un paletto si piantò nel duro e nero cuore di "
"Bodhi, colei che fu dannata in vita così come nella morte."

